headlines.description: — Myles Powell was on a layover in Dallas on his way to the G League showcase in Las Vegas when his agent FaceTimed to tell him he’d be signing with the Philadelphia 76ers as an emergency COVID-19 fill-in.
— DeMar DeRozan scored 26 points and the Chicago Bulls beat the Houston Rockets 133-118 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan, Bulls beat Rockets 133-118; win 2nd straight

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 23 points, Josh Giddey added 19 points and 11 assists, and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat Ja Morant and the Memphis Grizzlies 102-99 Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander, Thunder beat Grizz in Morant's return

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert had 23 points and 21 rebounds to lead the Utah Jazz to a 112-102 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz start fast, pull away late to beat Hornets 112-102

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Draymond Green and the Golden State Warriors gave his son an early 5th birthday gift by allowing the boy to help on the sidelines running towels, shooting shirts and masks to Warriors players along their bench.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry, Warriors beat Kings 113-98 in short-handed showdown

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray delivered his third triple-double in five games with 24 points, 13 assists and 12 rebounds, and the San Antonio Spurs beat the Los Angeles Clippers 116-92 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray's triple-double carries Spurs past Clippers, 116-92
